<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="357" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Bulgaria)/10–2745:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative in Bulgaria</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-27T00:00:00+02:00">October
                                    27, 1945—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received October 28—6:45
                                a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>642. General Crane informed orally by General Biryusov Russian
                            authorities will not clear Dr. Black<note n="84" xml:id="d357fn1">Floyd
                                H. Black, president, American College, Sofia.</note> into Bulgaria.
                            He said Black not sufficiently friendly to Russian objectives here. Do
                            not believe we should acquiesce this unjustifiable attitude. Recommend
                            vigorous protest both here and Moscow. Think it significant Biryusov has
                            not put his views in writing.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Istanbul as No. 8.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Barnes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>